# Plugin development

Contract: [plugins/types.js](plugins/types.js). HTML reference: [plugins/centralnovel/](plugins/centralnovel/).

Plugins are **source adapters** — HTML scraper, REST API, or hybrid. Not every plugin uses cheerio or PDF.

## Required

- `id` === folder name
- `name`, `setupFields`, `parseSeriesPage`, `resolvePdfUrl`
- Export: `export default plugin`

## Semantics (historical names)

- `parseSeriesPage(body)` — parse catalog from HTML **or** JSON string
- `resolvePdfUrl(chapterRef, ctx)` — resolve direct **asset** URL (PDF, image, …)
- `Chapter.pdfPageUrl` — opaque chapter reference, not necessarily a PDF URL

## Module layout

- `scraper.js` — HTML → catalog
- `catalog.js` — API/JSON → catalog
- `resolver.js` — chapterRef → asset URL

## Pitfalls

- Catalog keys must match `pluginConfig.volumes`
- Image plugins: core writes `.pdf` paths today — set `chapterContentType: 'image'` and plan core work
- Multi-image chapters need core extension (not one URL per chapter)
- Use `ctx.http` — not raw fetch

Full guide: [docs/PLUGIN_AUTHORING.md](docs/PLUGIN_AUTHORING.md)
